The Athletics Integrity Unit has banned 2008 Nigerian long jump silver medalist Blessing Okagbare, for 10 years over  doping. This was announced on Friday in a statement, stating that the Disciplinary Tribunal gave the declaration. The statement partly read, “The Disciplinary Tribunal has banned Nigerian sprinter Blessing Okagbare for a total of 10 years.” Tokyo Olympics: AFN Expresses Shock Over Okagbare’s Doping… [BREAKING] Tokyo Olympics: Okagbare Suspended After Testing… Recall that Okagbare was expelled from the Tokyo Olympics in 2021 after testing positive for human growth hormone at an out-of-competition test in Slovakia, before the women’s 100m semi-finals.